\cf0 \ul \ulc0 INTRODUCTION\ulnone \
\pard\pardeftab720
\cf0 \
After the death of Solomon, the 12 tribes of Israel divide.\
They divide into 10 tribes in the north, and 2 tribes in the south. (Judah/Benjamin)\
The 10 in the north turned away from the Lord first.\
They were taken captive by the Assyrians in 722 BC.\
The 2 tribes in the south formed the nation called Judah with Jerusalem as its capital.\
Ezekiel is in Judah.\
Ezekiel refers to them as Israelites.\
In Ezekiel\'92s lifetime, they were all that were left of the original nation Israel.\
Judah became as bad, if not worse, than the 10 tribes in the north.\
In 598 BC King Nebuchudnezzer of Babylon attacked Judah.\
They hung on for 3 months, after which the king of Judah, Jehoiachin, handed the city over.\
In 597 Nebuchudnezzer took them all captive to Babylon.\
Among these captives, was Ezekiel.\
Nebuchudnezzer left Jehoiachin\'92s uncle, Zedakiah in charge of Jerusalem.\
Zedakiah was not loyal to Nebuchudnezzer and so in 586 BC Jerusalem is destroyed.\
The Babylonians killed most of the people in Jerusalem but took some to Babylon.\
\
