\cf0 \ul \ulc0 CONSECRATION\ulnone \
\pard\pardeftab720
\cf0 \
What is consecration?\
\
Well first of all let's say what it's not, none of which happens here in GIC.\
\
Never was a believer brought into healthy spiritual maturity by means of pressure at some meeting or gathering of some kind.\
\
This subject of consecration seems to be badly misunderstood by so many believers. Many, especially those young in the Lord, have been victimised time and time again in this matter of surrender, or commitment. \
\
Most likely by something like, \'93The Lord Jesus gave His all for you, now the least you can do is give your all for Him\'94.\
\
The believer is exhorted and pressured to consecrate, surrender, commit his life to Christ on the basis of his love and gratitude for what has been done at Calvary.\
\
How often is the average congregation put through this routine.\
How often is the individual believer manoeuvred down the front of the church to consecrate and reconsecrate, surrender and re-surrender, commit and re-commit to Christ.\
\uc0\u8232 Why is it that after a while the believer comes to dread such meetings and messages?\
Well, there are a number of reasons and there are also plenty of scriptural answers.\
\
First, it is completely futile to expect a believer to take the giant leap from his ground of substitution (Rom 3 \'96 5), to the identification truth of (Rom 6 \'96 7) onto that of the deeper truths found in Rom 8 and 12:1.\
\
Now its true that every hungry hearted believer longs for effective life and service for God. But until hard experience teaches him otherwise, the well meaning believer thinks that since he has the will to obey God, he should attempt to carry it out through personal consecrated effort with the help of the Lord.\
\
In other words, he tries to struggle forward via the love motive, ie, He did for me, so I must do for Him.\
\
Now here is something very useful to understand about all this.\
The new believer, and the new man he now is in Christ is a permanent gift from God.\
The believer gains a brand new will, a will of the nature of the new man in Christ.\
\
However, the power to do is not a permanent gift!\
\
But it must be received moment by moment from the Holy Spirit.\
Pause!\
\
As growing Christians its time for us to see the necessity of going beyond the love motive 
\b to the life motive
\b0 . 
\i For to me to live is Christ 
\i0 Phil 1:21. \
\
\
The question is which life is to be consecrated to Him?\
The old self life, or the new Christ life?\
Since God can accept nothing from the old, it is the new.\
Therefore, God has put one condition before us regarding consecration.\
\
\'93
\i present yourselves to God, as being alive from the dead\'94
\i0  Rom 6:13.\
\
This is our only ground and we are to count ourselves dead to sin, self, the law, the world, and alive to God in Christ who is risen.\
We are to walk in newness of life, it is a risen life.\
\uc0\u8232 So now with consecration established we can go on to more.\
\
So God separates us to Himself. He consecrates us. He chooses us. But why?\
