But it is so much more than that, it's less of us, and more of Him.\
If our sign demonstrates or portrays someone other than God, then we have failed.\
We must always keep that in mind.\
And that will be our main focus this morning as we go through the message for today.\
Consecration is the cement used to fuse together God's purpose for us and in us, in order for us to become a sign, and vessel for God.\
\
Now it is God in His eternal purpose who determines how He manifests Himself in our mortal flesh. In doing so, He would somehow bring about a sign in this world, that would signify something of Himself, His infinite Wisdom, Eternal Power, and Glory in us.\
\
Imagine that, God taking hold of a man, and in that man, moulding and shaping that man through many trials and tribulations and by so doing, He makes a statement for Himself and for His purposes that says, \'93Look at him, and learn\'94.\
